---
import MarketingLayout from "../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="How it works"
  description="See how CategoryFix moves from scan to review, apply, and rollback without hiding uncertainty."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Workflow</p>
    <h1>Scan, review, apply, and roll back with the same trust model end to end.</h1>
    <p>
      CategoryFix is built around a simple rule: changes should stay explainable before they become
      scalable. The workflow keeps that principle visible from the first scan through rollback.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">The four-step loop</p>
        <h2>How merchants work with the product today</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="steps-grid">
      <article class="step">
        <p class="kicker">1. Scan</p>
        <h3>Run a product scan</h3>
        <p>
          Bulk product reads gather the current category state and the catalog signals needed for
          deterministic matching.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="step">
        <p class="kicker">2. Review</p>
        <h3>Inspect the reasons</h3>
        <p>
          Findings show recommendation basis, confidence labels, and whether the item is safe for
          default bulk selection or needs extra review.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="step">
        <p class="kicker">3. Apply</p>
        <h3>Confirm category writes</h3>
        <p>
          Apply jobs execute only after explicit merchant confirmation. The workflow focuses on what
          will change, not just that something can change.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="step">
        <p class="kicker">4. Roll back</p>
        <h3>Reverse when needed</h3>
        <p>
          Rollback jobs use stored evidence from the original change, keeping reversal available
          inside the product surface.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Edge cases</p>
        <h2>What happens when the system is not sure</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="docs-grid">
      <article>
        <h3>No safe deterministic recommendation</h3>
        <p>
          The product can say exactly that and leave the product unchanged. It does not force a
          suggestion where the rules cannot defend one.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Optional AI fallback</h3>
        <p>
          If AI assistance is enabled, it is used only as supporting context for deterministic
          no-safe results, never as silent platform truth.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
